1
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:09,900
(Love begins with an emotional spark.)

2
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:10,840
Still him.

3
00:00:11,290 --> 00:00:12,300
The one who you like most?

4
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:13,000
Yeah.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,110
I swear, you're the one and only.

6
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:16,600
If you're happy, then I'm happy.

7
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:19,840
Cheers.

8
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:23,940
(But lasting love needs rational insight.)

9
00:00:24,710 --> 00:00:25,360
Many times,

10
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:26,150
our hearts

11
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:29,000
know the truth before our minds do.

12
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:30,920
That's kinda scary.

13
00:00:31,310 --> 00:00:35,200
This experiment isn't about judging
or exposing anyone.

14
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:37,110
Are you lying?

15
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:39,910
It's meant to help them clear away

16
00:00:39,910 --> 00:00:42,150
the fog around their expression

17
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:45,200
and see each other's truest reactions.

18
00:00:45,630 --> 00:00:47,720
Each person must take

19
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,910
a polygraph test.

20
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:52,560
Together, we'll discover

21
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,270
the secrets of genuine feelings

22
00:00:54,270 --> 00:00:55,840
unfolded through our bodies.

23
00:00:57,180 --> 00:01:01,020
=Episode 7 (Part 1)=
=Lie or Truth=

24
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:01,880
The polygraph.

25
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:03,430
Could it be the kind

26
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:04,490
that clips onto your hand

27
00:01:04,630 --> 00:01:06,080
and zaps you whenever you lie?

28
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:07,630
I'm curious about

29
00:01:07,630 --> 00:01:08,890
the questions they're gonna ask.

30
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,310
Hope the machine

31
00:01:10,310 --> 00:01:11,550
doesn't expose me.

32
00:01:11,550 --> 00:01:12,510
What lie did you tell?

33
00:01:12,830 --> 00:01:13,630
I didn't...

34
00:01:13,630 --> 00:01:13,910
Well,

35
00:01:14,170 --> 00:01:15,480
I don't want to know the result.

36
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,690
I have no idea what they're gonna ask.

37
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:19,310
You could ask Yang.

38
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,480
But me asking Jiayi feels awkward,

39
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,000
honestly.

40
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,760
If I ask sharp questions,

41
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,910
she'd start to dislike me.

42
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,410
Do you have any questions?

43
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:28,590
Are you scared of it?

44
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,080
Maybe a little bit.

45
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:31,630
Are you scared?

46
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:32,590
No, I'm not.

47
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,120
I'm just worried

48
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,550
that it might mess up.

49
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:37,440
Why?

50
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,990
Do you have any concerns?

51
00:01:39,550 --> 00:01:40,230
No, none at all.

52
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:41,000
I'm just imagining.

53
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:44,120
Sir.

54
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:46,820
(Ji Yu, psychological counselor)

55
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:47,990
(Area of practice: relationship issues)

56
00:01:47,990 --> 00:01:48,480
Have a seat.

57
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:50,760
Professor.

58
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,180
You're professional.

59
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:52,910
Cool.

60
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:54,440
We'll start in a bit.

61
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,510
Everyone needs to undergo

62
00:01:56,510 --> 00:01:57,630
a polygraph

63
00:01:58,310 --> 00:01:58,760
test.

64
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,100
(Polygraph with Multimodal Physiological Data
Acquisition & Analysis System)

65
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:00,690
(Powered by proprietary AI algorithms.)

66
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:01,470
(Collects indicators from EDA,
pulse rate, respiration,)

67
00:02:01,470 --> 00:02:02,160
(video-based physiological signals,
and micro-movements.)

68
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:02,730
(Provides data support for
psychological assessment and interrogations)

69
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:03,380
(Accuracy rate: approx. 80%)

70
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,110
That's interesting.

71
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:11,390
It's my first time.

72
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,110
Me too.

73
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,630
Before we officially start,

74
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:17,670
we need to do a prep work.

75
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,520
Let's have some warm water first.

76
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:21,550
This way,

77
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:23,080
it helps the polygraph

78
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:25,360
capture more accurately

79
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,030
the electrical signals
your bodies give off.

80
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,390
Here, pass this over.

81
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:34,960
Come on.

82
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:35,720
Here.

83
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,000
Yijia.

84
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:38,390
It's pretty hot.

85
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:39,750
Why so nervous?

86
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,000
Why?

87
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:43,730
Because I don't know

88
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,270
what you're about to ask.

89
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:50,830
Even those not asking questions
seem excited.

90
00:02:50,830 --> 00:02:51,240
Yeah.

91
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:55,360
I think I'm a genuine person.

92
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,470
I don't think

93
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,880
this polygraphy

94
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:02,080
would flag me.

95
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,320
Yeah.

96
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,800
My heart's racing
before the test eve starts.

97
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,130
Can it be accurate?

98
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,720
This polygraph we use

99
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:08,800
can detect

100
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,470
whether you're nervous

101
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,880
or you're lying.

102
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,440
It can tell the differences.

103
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:16,630
Impressive.

104
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:16,910
Nice.

105
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:17,550
Cool.

106
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:17,830
Nice.

107
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,600
Who wants to try it first?

108
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,470
Me.

109
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:22,960
I wanna try.

110
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:29,390
Alright, put these finger sleeves on.

111
00:03:29,390 --> 00:03:29,750
Here.

112
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:31,240
Finger sleeves

113
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,030
can detect changes

114
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:34,520
of electrodermal activity and assess
one's emotional state

115
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,490
like tension or anxiety.

116
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,320
Alright.

117
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,600
Take a moment to calm yourself.

118
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,190
I'll ask.

119
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:43,600
Okay.

120
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:44,520
Sit.

121
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,520
Do you see me as just your sister?

122
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:48,470
What?

123
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,880
Do you see me as just your sister?

124
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:50,550
That's hilarious.

125
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:51,880
Hey, brother.

126
00:03:52,630 --> 00:03:53,160
Hey, sis.

127
00:03:53,670 --> 00:03:53,990
Hold on.

128
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:55,550
(Huang Jiawei. Chen Family)
Let him calm down.

129
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:56,880
He's a bit nervous.

130
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,910
He got nervous the moment it started.

131
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,670
Do you still have feelings for your ex?

132
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,500
(Do you still have feelings for your ex?)

133
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,520
He told me that day,

134
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,880
his ex looked kinda like

135
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,720
a mix between Christy Chung

136
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:12,960
and Cecilia Cheung.

137
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,000
That's pretty fun.

138
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,920
Yeah, I think so too.

139
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,200
No.

140
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:31,580
(Do you still have feelings for your ex?
No.)

141
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,230
The polygraph shows he's lying.

142
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:39,300
(Detected as a lie)

143
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,040
Oh no.

144
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,110
His image just collapsed.

145
00:04:41,110 --> 00:04:41,760
Totally doomed.

146
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:46,230
Guess I know you best, brother.

147
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,720
No way.

148
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,200
I never believed

149
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,200
