152
00:04:56,550 --> 00:04:57,510
So I don't buy it.

153
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:00,380
(Fool your bros if you must,
not yourself.)

154
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:03,790
Any more questions?

155
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:04,440
I've got one.

156
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:07,790
Alright.

157
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,440
Is there any women at present

158
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,160
whom you want to know more

159
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,270
about?

160
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,230
No.

161
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,720
The polygraph shows

162
00:05:19,230 --> 00:05:20,390
he's lying.

163
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:24,220
(Detected as a lie)

164
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:25,230
No way.

165
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:27,070
Bro.

166
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:27,550
No way.

167
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,550
No one would believe me.

168
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,760
You're lying to your own friends?

169
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,880
I didn't lie to you.

170
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,040
Calm down, take a breath.

171
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,480
The graph's a bit messy.

172
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,420
His minds wanders.

173
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,670
Who do you want to know about,

174
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:44,230
Jiawei?

175
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,500
She asked if there's any female guests

176
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,670
I'd like to know more about.

177
00:05:50,670 --> 00:05:51,350
I said no.

178
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:52,270
It showed I was lying.

179
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,330
Not accurate.

180
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:55,270
Impossible.

181
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:57,790
Okay.

182
00:05:58,110 --> 00:05:59,390
So, who's gonna ask the question?

183
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:00,510
Me.

184
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:01,350
Me.

185
00:06:01,350 --> 00:06:02,100
(Brother's revenge)

186
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:04,230
Sis,

187
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:05,270
do you still have feelings

188
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,600
for your

189
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,440
ex-boyfriend?

190
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,950
(Still hung up on your ex?)

191
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,440
Sibling rivalry getting brutal here.

192
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:12,720
No, I don't.

193
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,760
The polygraph shows

194
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,950
an obvious lie.

195
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:21,140
(Detected as a lie)

196
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:21,510
Lie.

197
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,040
A very obvious lie.

198
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,920
How could you

199
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,920
laugh at me?

200
00:06:26,230 --> 00:06:26,640
Sis.

201
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:30,790
That's definitely fake.

202
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,390
Totally fake.

203
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,790
I can't believe it.

204
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,230
It showed I was lying?

205
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:37,320
I can't believe this.

206
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,790
There's a delay

207
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,760
(Expert's explanation)
of your reaction.

208
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,040
Then it'll show the real

209
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:44,760
data changes.

210
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:46,550
My reflex is way too slow.

211
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:48,880
Means you're thinking about

212
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,040
the question.

213
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,230
So professional.

214
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:52,480
Who else wants to try?

215
00:06:52,790 --> 00:06:53,110
Me.

216
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:54,270
Seriously?

217
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,640
Who wants to throw him a question?

218
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,600
Please sit here.

219
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:01,830
Okay.

220
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,930
(Wu Guanjie. Zhu Huiyan)
Ask a random question first.

221
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,040
Anything?

222
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:05,830
Yeah.

223
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,040
Do you like the color red?

224
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,390
You can answer yes or no.

225
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,440
No in-between option?

226
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,390
He doesn't have

227
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:21,230
feelings about it.

228
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,350
He's pretty honest.

229
00:07:22,350 --> 00:07:23,550
Is there any in-between option?

230
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:26,230
Then…

231
00:07:26,230 --> 00:07:26,920
Yes.

232
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:31,300
(Do you like the color red? Yes.)

233
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,390
That's a lie.

234
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:33,830
You're lying.

235
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:34,950
(Detected as a lie)

236
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:35,790
He lied.

237
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:37,000
So yeah, that was a lie.

238
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:43,510
Would you be more proactive next time?

239
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:45,830
Yes.

240
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,480
No.

241
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,320
He shock his head.

242
00:07:59,110 --> 00:08:00,200
That's a lie.

243
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,550
(Detected as a lie)

244
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:02,880
Are you lying?

245
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,450
Even the rain couldn't bear it.

246
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,640
I'm speechless

247
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,880
and also a bit awkward.

248
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:28,040
Hard to tell if he's acting or for real.

249
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,160
I'm hesitant to keep asking.

250
00:08:34,710 --> 00:08:36,710
Have you ever had feelings for me?

251
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,640
Yeah.

252
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,200
That made me even more nervous.

253
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,320
According to the polygraph reading,

254
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,440
you're telling the truth.

255
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:57,300
(Detected as truth)

256
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,440
You're done for.

257
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,320
Done for how?

258
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,000
You lied to me.

259
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,000
About what?

260
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,640
You're done for.

261
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,760
I don't want to talk to you.

262
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:05,320
Earlier,

263
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,000
I wasn't serious.

264
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,520
Then, I paused for a second

265
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,000
to think.

266
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,440
Yeah.

267
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,030
And I answered.

268
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,230
It showed truth.

269
00:09:12,710 --> 00:09:13,840
Let me do it, sir.

270
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:20,520
Sitting there made me nervous.

271
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:22,760
My heart started racing for a bit.

272
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:34,000
Have you felt your heart flutter
on the island?

273
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:40,060
(Felt moved on the island?)

274
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,880
Yes.

275
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:44,880
She's telling the truth.

276
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,550
(Detected as truth)

277
00:09:46,550 --> 00:09:48,200
What kind of question is that?

278
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,350
I...

279
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:54,350
Next question.

280
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:55,440
There's a second one?

281
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:56,960
Nice.

282
00:09:58,710 --> 00:10:01,110
Do you feel drawn to Tianyu?

283
00:10:01,420 --> 00:10:06,820
(Do you feel drawn to Tianyu?)

284
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:12,790
Yes.

285
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:17,960
She's telling the truth.

286
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:22,260
(Detected as truth)

287
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:28,960
Any more questions?

288
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:34,670
I don't want to put pressure on her.

289
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:36,470
Some things are best felt by yourself.

290
00:10:38,670 --> 00:10:39,470
Any other questions?

291
00:10:39,470 --> 00:10:39,880
Anyone

292
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:40,840
asking me a question?

293
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:44,000
I'm really nervous.

294
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:46,470
Alright, I'll ask one.

295
00:10:46,470 --> 00:10:46,760
Sure.

296
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,640
Come here.

